There are two main forms of transport running through our area.
Number 1:-{THE RAILWAY. The railway runs from Southampton to Bournemouth. The station is sited in the top central section of our area and the railway runs vertically through the right hand side of the map.{(Sections 2,6,11)}
Number 2:-{THE ROAD.} This is the A35 which is a major road in the south. The road runs across the top left hand side of our grid. The road is busy as it carries traffic to the New Forest and to the campsite in our area.{(Sections 2,5)
